---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { t } from '../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="About" locale={locale}>
  <main class="site-main">
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h1 class="section-title">About Parallaxin</h1>
        <p class="section-desc">Documentation of the distance between what power says and what power does.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-content">
        <h3>The Lens Metaphor</h3>
        <p>
          Parallax is the displacement or difference in the apparent position of an object viewed 
          along two different lines of sight. In power dynamics, there is often a massive parallax 
          between <strong>stated positions</strong> (diplomatic cables, press releases, public speeches) 
          and <strong>documented actions</strong> (military movements, budget allocations, verified footage).
        </p>
        <p>
          Parallaxin is the lens through which we document that gap.
        </p>

        <h3>What makes us different?</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Evidence-based, not consensus-based:</strong> We don't wait for "official confirmation" if the verifiable evidence already exists. We don't seek a middle ground between a fact and a lie.</li>
          <li><strong>The Gap is the Product:</strong> Our primary focus is the actor-behavior gap. We document what changed between the claim and the action.</li>
          <li><strong>Ungovernable by Design:</strong> Parallaxin is open source and hosted as a static site. It has no centralized database to seize, no accounts to ban, and no single point of failure.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>How it's built</h3>
        <p>
          Parallaxin is built on openness and auditability.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Open Source:</strong> Everything from the site engine to the data schema is available on GitHub under the MIT license.</li>
          <li><strong>Static Site:</strong> The site is pre-rendered for speed, security, and permanence.</li>
          <li><strong>Git as Audit Trail:</strong> Every change to every record is tracked in public Git commits, creating a permanent, immutable record of our own documentation process.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>The Constitution</h3>
        <p>
          All editorial decisions and operational principles are governed by the 
          <a href={base + 'constitution'}>Parallaxin Constitution</a>. 
          It defines our methodology for sourcing, inference, and error correction.
        </p>

        <h3>How to Contribute</h3>
        <p>
          We welcome contributions from researchers, developers, and translators. Please see our 
          <a href="https://github.com/parallaxin/parallaxin/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">CONTRIBUTING.md</a> 
          on GitHub for guidelines on how to submit evidence, fix bugs, or add new features.
        </p>

        <h3>Contact</h3>
        <p>
          For security vulnerabilities, please email: 
          <a href="mailto:parallaxin@proton.me">parallaxin@proton.me</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          For all other communication, including content disputes or feature requests, please 
          <strong>open an issue on GitHub</strong>. We do not handle editorial or technical 
          discussions via email to maintain a transparent public record.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .section {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .about-content {
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
  .about-content h3 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .about-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }
  .about-content ul {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }
  .about-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .about-content a {
    color: var(--color-documented);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .about-content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
